parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Pad Wear and Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature brake pad wear and ABS issues can lead to reduced stopping power, increased stopping distances, and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Brake pads wear down rapidly
ABS warning lights illuminate
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
emergency brake assist activates independently
and warning messages indicate objects in front of the vehicle when there are none.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the manual parking brake can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Manual parking brake releases fully when parked uphill
even when applied tightly
resulting in the vehicle moving or rolling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Complete brake failure can lead to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Brakes fail to slow down or stop the vehicle
resulting in collisions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Start-Stop System can cause the vehicle to stall at a stop light, leading to unexpected loss of power and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle's engine turns off unexpectedly
requiring manual restart
notification on the dashboard stating "Please start engine manually"
and failure to accelerate when the accelerator is pressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loss of power and acceleration can cause the vehicle to slow down unexpectedly, leading to potential accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power and accelerates slower than normal
the check engine warning indicator illuminates
and failure codes pertain to the loss of camshaft synchronization and failure of cylinder two.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission issues can cause the vehicle to jerk or hesitate, leading to loss of control or unexpected movements.
symptoms: The transmission shifts roughly
the brake pedal brakes harder than supposed to
making the car jerky
and the engine vibrates excessively when idling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden shattering of the sunroof can cause driver distraction, loss of control, and potential accidents, as well as injury from shattered glass.
symptoms: Loud "boom" or cracking sound
sudden shattering of the sunroof
no apparent reason or external impact
no warning signs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The random activation of the Front Assist system can cause sudden braking, loss of control, and potential accidents, especially on empty roads or in gentle curves.
symptoms: False forward collision warnings
sudden braking without any apparent reason
activation of the warning sound
no other vehicles or obstacles in sight.
